File: Finance Minister Tito Mboweni ahead of 2020 National Budget speech in Parliament, Cape Town. JOHANNESBURG - Finance Minister, Tito Mboweni's Medium-Term Budget Policy Statement is set to be delayed by at least a week. Mboweni sent his request for the postponement to National Assembly Speaker, Thandi Modise on Tuesday evening. The mini-budget was scheduled for 21 October. READ:Â SA economy could shrink more than forecast: Mboweni Last year's Medium-Term Budget Policy Statement was also postponed by a week due to international commitments. Mboweni says this year's postponement is because of delays in the finalisation of the economic reconstruction and recovery plan. Mboweni now wants the budget tabled on 28 October.